ce:section.ce:para:
In the present work, a series of Sm3+ activated YAO NPs and CDs encapsulated in YAO:3Sm3+ NCs are successfully synthesized through hydrothermal assisted combustion method. The CDs integrated YAO:Sm3+ NCs exhibit orange-red light. Additionally, the energy transfer from CDs to Sm3+ increases the emission intensity of Sm3+. Despite the fact that the emission intensity of 5 wt% CDs@YAO:3Sm3+ NCs increased by a factor of 18.2, FRET between CDs and the luminous Sm3+ may be the reason behind this enhancement. In optical thermometry, the YAO:Sm3+ NPs and 5 wt% CDs@YAO:3Sm3+ NCs exhibited impressive relative and absolute sensitivity values (S

                        r
                     ) of 0.13 and 0.11 % K−1, (S

                        a
                     ) of 0.0013 and 0.0011 K−1 respectively. The lifetime values are determined to be 3.072 ms for YAO:3Sm3+ NPs and 4.10 ms for 5 wt % CDs@YAO:3Sm3+ NCs. In real-world applications, the powder dusting method shows to be the most promising way to develop LFPs. It has many benefits, including as ease of use, speed, high sensitivity, cost-effectiveness, and adaptability for large-scale operations. It is also not restricted by substrate types. The results show that orange-red pigment-made AC labels are very stable in a range of ambient conditions. With more possibilities for expanding the spectrum of stimulation types, this sophisticated AC security label offers increased versatility in optical AC technology.
